title: Age structure in Uganda 2018
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 3 lines representing 0-14 years, 15-64 years, and 65 years and older. The y axis denotes Share of total population and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall 0-14 years, 15-64 years, and 65 years and older are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. 15-64 years, 2. 0-14 years, and lastly, 3. 65 years and older.
Overall across the Year, 15-64 years mostly maintained the highest Share of total population when compared to others with a mean value of 49.73, and it peaked at 2018.
After 15-64 years, 0-14 years overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 48.3, peaking at 2008.
65 years and older mostly had the least Share of total population with a mean value of 1.89, which peaked at 2018 with a value of 1.94.
